company_description:
AI ROI stalls when decisions can’t be traced. Deepentix converts unstructured documents into a verifiable Claim Graph, linking every answer back to its evidence (“Answer → Claim → Paragraph → Document → Author”). Our reasoning plane goes beyond basic RAG: graph-constrained retrieval, counterfactual checks (e.g., policy clauses, CER criteria), and paragraph-level citations minimize hallucinations and make audits fast. We’re EU-AI-Act–ready by design.
We focus first on MedTech/Pharma (e.g., Clinical Evaluation Reports, protocol reviews) and Insurance (coverage assessment, underwriting), where manual reviews are slow, fragmented, and hard to audit. Traction to date includes a live Gap Finder, shipped Claim Graph API, pilots in MedTech and Insurance, and non-dilutive DeepTech funding. The outcome for customers: shorter reviews, higher straight-through processing, and defensible decisions with full provenance.
shortDescription: Scientific claim verification platform

Beyond NT-proBNP, our platform is designed to expand to additional biomarkers — including renal function (eGFR) — creating the first scalable AI platform for digital biomarker diagnostics. company_description:
Wemates introduces an innovative P2P risk-sharing platform, which operates purely as a technical intermediary, adeptly connecting individuals seeking equitable and transparent insurance alternatives.
In essence, we’re building a P2P risk-sharing network where a group of individuals with mutual interests or similar risk profiles pool their “premiums” together to insure against a risk. Our platform enables individuals with similar interests to share the risk between themselves, whether based on shared interests, community ties, or specific needs. Often these individuals are somehow connected, e.g. personally (friends), or through mutual business or other common criteria (e.g. possession or similar interests). These groups are then free to define their terms, set coverage limits, and even manage claims. That significantly diverges from traditional insurance
models by community-centric insurance ecosystem, utilizing decentralization and advanced technologies.
shortDescription: Wemates introduces an innovative P2P risk-sharing platform, which operates purely as a technical intermediary, adeptly connecting individuals seeking equitable and transparent insurance alternatives.

company_description:
What does your company do?
Wormsensing develops and commercializes the world’s most sensitive and compact piezoceramic sensors to monitor vibration and deformation in real time. Our flagship product, Dragonfly®, enables unprecedented insight into the mechanical behavior of machines — from aerospace engines to manufacturing lines. Thanks to its ultra-thin format, plug & play design, and extreme sensitivity (1000× over legacy sensors), Dragonfly® captures what traditional sensors miss: subtle deformation signals at the source, even on moving or embedded parts. This data is then processed through our software stack, enabling predictive maintenance, quality control, and structural health monitoring across R&D, Industry 4.0, and OEM applications. With over 40 patents, strong traction (+110% YoY), and a proven in-house production capacity (2M units/year), Wormsensing bridges physical performance with digital intelligence — for a safer, smarter, more efficient industry.
prominent_investors: INNOVACOM, KBC Focus Fund, Cea investment
shortDescription: Wormsensing develops advanced vibration sensors and the Dragonfly platform, enabling precise acoustic pattern recognition and integrated physiological measurements for industries including aerospace, robotics, healthcare, automotive, and energy.

We are developing a platform that allows anyone to easily fine-tune small language model (SLMs). 
How easily? Imagine writing an in-context learning prompt to an LLM with a few dozen examples.

Such specialized SLMs can solve specific tasks at much lower latency and cost than generic, pre-trained LLMs while maintaining accuracy. Additionally their small size allow for local deployment – leveraging the benefits of CPU inference (speed, cost, security, networking, reduced dependencies).

Our hypothesis is that such small models will be the building blocks of highly performant multi-agentic AI products of the future.

company_description: Smabbler Galaxia is the first hypergraph-based AI system that autonomously transforms massive unstructured data into fully explainable knowledge graphs - enabling AI models to reason, retain context, and provide traceable answers at scale. Unlike traditional LLMs or RAG pipelines that rely on probabilistic outputs and limited context windows, Galaxia builds a persistent semantic memory layer that eliminates hallucinations and delivers deterministic, auditable intelligence. It operates entirely in-memory on CPUs, processing over 120,000 pages in a single pass without GPUs or complex infrastructure. This allows enterprises in life sciences, finance, compliance, and other regulated sectors to build AI solutions that are not only powerful, but trusted, transparent, and deployment-ready in hours instead of months. Our mission is to redefine AI from black-box predictions to explainable intelligence that businesses can rely on for critical decision-making.

Seerlinq is a MedTech startup that provides the world’s first certified non-invasive, AI-powered home monitoring system for cardiac filling pressures based PPG signal analysis, enabling early detection and prevention of heart failure decompensation.

By analyzing photoplethysmographic (PPG) signals through simple devices like smartwatches or oximeters, Seerlinq allows physicians to detect worsening heart failure up to 30 days in advance, reducing hospitalizations by over 70%—all without implants or invasive procedures.

Key elements of what Seerlinq does:
- Offers remote, continuous monitoring of heart failure patients
- Uses AI and pathophysiology-based algorithms to assess cardiac pressures
- Supports early clinical intervention before symptoms appear
- Enables affordable, scalable telemedicine with full reimbursement in some markets
- Aims to transform chronic heart failure management with personalized care

But you can't remember - an average home has over 300 000 items. That's why a detailed home inventory can increase insurance payouts by up to 50%, meaning tens or even hundreds of thousands of dollars more in compensation.

But creating an inventory manually is tedious and takes days to create. That's why we built ReEmber, the world's first efforless inventory solution.

With ReEmber, the user just takes a walkthough video of their home, opening all cabinets and drawers. Our app then detects and recognizes every item and lists them in a insurance-ready inventory with proof of ownership and estimated replacement costs. In just 15-30 minutes you'll have peace of mind.

And there's so much more ReEmber can do, once we have the data of all your household items.

InSpek is solving these inefficiencies with the first AI-driven bioprocess optimization platform that doesn’t just analyse data – but also collects it. Our patented on-chip optical sensors, developed at MIT, capture rich, real-time process data at any scale. This fuels AI models that identify optimal process parameters, enabling higher yields, lower costs, and faster scale-up.
We are building the intelligence layer for biomanufacturing – accelerating the shift from trial-and-error to data-driven industrial biology.

It connects wearable data, recovery signals, and training load into a unified experience — providing adaptive training plans, personalized insights, and streamlined communication.
Athletes gain real-time guidance. Coaches get visibility and control.
We’ve launched our MVP, onboarded first paying athletes and coaches, and are building momentum with pilot clubs in Finland and Nordic Countries. 

Most tools focus either on athletes (e.g. Strava, Garmin Connect) or coaches (e.g. Final Surge, TrainingPeaks).
But the future of sport is collaborative and data-driven.
TrainFlow bridges this gap with a shared platform for both sides — helping teams and individuals adjust workload based on HRV, sleep, fatigue, and stress signals.
No more spreadsheets. No guesswork. Just smarter performance.

The technology was developed under a UK government research grant and in association with the world's leading sleep scientists, including Apple's former head of sleep - it is being integrated into luxury hotels and we are launching a consumer beta in 2026.

company_description:
FrostForge cuts the cord on cooling, making ice from sunlight 🧊☀️. No fuel, no electricity, simply cool. We're transforming cooling infrastructure to be grid-independent, cost-effective, and climate-resilient. 

Cooling is critical to modern life: food, vaccines, data. But it’s costly, power-hungry, and failing as heat outpaces infrastructure. Cold chain failures cost global supply chains over $1 trillion annually in spoiled food, compromised medicines, and disrupted operations. 

FrostForge flips the equation: we make ice from sunlight. No grid. No fuel. No wires. Simply cool.
With sub-zero cooling, food distributors, vaccine suppliers, and cold storage operators cut costs, preserve product, and build resilient supply chains where they need them. 

With rising temperatures and net-zero mandates, traditional cooling infrastructure is becoming economically and environmentally unsustainable.
shortDescription: FrostForge develops sustainable, off-grid cooling solutions that prioritize eco-friendly innovation and offer updates on their products through their website.

company_description: Vizaible helps brands understand and improve how Generative AI systems like ChatGPT, Gemini, Claude, and Perplexity perceive them. As AI replaces traditional search, most companies have become invisible — their products, claims, and differentiators are not recalled by large language models. Vizaible solves this through a full Generative-Engine Optimization (GEO) stack: it audits a brand’s visibility across major AIs, identifies claim gaps between what the company says and what AIs remember, and then activates structured microsites, schema, and FAQs that feed correct data back into the AI ecosystem. The platform also tracks visibility evolution, authority, and recall performance over time. Powered by a tokenized credit economy, every audit and activation fuels both monetization and network growth. In short, Vizaible turns AI perception into a measurable, fixable, and monetizable business asset.
prominent_investors: Orange Belgium

At Automata, we saw how in nature, solutions to complex problems emerge from order, with just tiny bits of wisdom. So we started to build something totally different from existing software engineering paradigms.

company_description:
Who we are
Velionis is a mobility safety startup developing aftermarket driver monitoring solutions that fuse hardware sensors with AI. Our flagship product, the CozyArm handlebar, integrates a capacitive Hands-On-Detection (HOD) sensor and a breath alcohol module to track steering contact and alcohol levels in real time.

What we build
Through the Wheel&Cash app and fleet dashboard, we apply computer vision and rPPG algorithms using either an IR camera or a standard smartphone camera. This enables reliable drowsiness detection, fatigue prediction, and heart-rate monitoring, with instant driver alerts and event-only uploads that protect privacy.

Why it matters
Guided by the vision “See the invisible, prevent the unforeseen,” Velionis addresses the fast-growing demand for affordable ADAS/DMS solutions. We are running PoC pilots with logistics and taxi operators, while preparing for scale-up across Europe, the U.S. Our goal is to reduce accidents, lower insurance costs.

company_description: XRlabs is building the software platform that powers the future of surgery. We combine extended reality, deep surgical vision, and low-power edge AI to enable surgeons to rehearse, plan, and operate with patient-specific precision. Our system runs on commercially available headsets and uses a proprietary hybrid tracking method—fusing wireless displacement sensors with real-time visual mapping—to achieve sub-millimeter accuracy, even when tools are inside the body or out of sight. Each case generates a unique paired dataset: a preoperative rehearsal and a live procedure, which together train our foundation model (XRbrain) for continuous improvement. Already deployed in complex neurosurgical cases, including the world’s first AI-designed MR prostheses used in conjoined twin separation, XRlabs is delivering real clinical value today—while laying the foundation for shared-control robotics and semi-autonomous surgical systems tomorrow.

company_description:
The productivity revolution driven by AI can only succeed if AI can access and process a company’s internal data and documents with near-perfect accuracy. However, implementing this reliably is technically very challenging. 

That’s why ByteIT offers a data pipeline that converts information from all common formats, including scans and image files, into what’s known as a RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation) database. From these databases, language models such as ChatGPT can retrieve and process information without the need for costly retraining or fine-tuning.

Building and reading such databases at a high level of quality requires advanced AI. ByteIT relies particularly on Visual Language Models (VLMs) – a new generation of AI models that can understand the content and structure of documents much more effectively.

company_description:
Automatic medical papers review.

Our service, Library Med, is similar to Wolfram Alpha, but for biomedicine rather than mathematics. It deconstructs researches into phases and components, each receiving a score from a set of IT and AI tools. The score is based on methodological standards. Better the component adherence to its ideal standard, the better the score.
Finally, the score is justified in detail for every component analyzed. Many papers can be analyzed, compared and automatically aggregated (automatic meta-analysis). This aids doctors and students in swiftly and cheaply accessing robust literature and empowers researchers to enhance their work's empirical rigor, boosting publication prospects. 
It is the first technological step towards the first decentralized scientific publication network.
shortDescription: Library Med leverages AI to analyze, score, and justify biomedical research based on methodological standards, enabling efficient literature access, automatic meta-analysis, and improved research rigor for doctors, students, and scientists.

BIONCaRT is seeking for  series A investments in spring 2026.

company_description:
Our circular batteries help buildings, industries, and EV chargers cut energy bills by up to 40%, ensure reliable power, and unlock new revenue from grid services, delivering a payback of 2.7 years and up to 5x returns.

By reusing the 80%+ remaining capacity of EV batteries with our unique technology, we provide fire-safe systems that match the price, performance, and warranties of new batteries, while avoiding up to 100 tons of CO2 per system.

This model also addresses a growing imbalance in the energy sector: global supply of second-life batteries is set to exceed demand for stationary storage. We do not need to produce new batteries to meet future needs, we simply reuse the high-value resources already available.

By scaling our technology through local battery streams worldwide, we can realize our vision of democratizing access to sustainable, affordable energy. And the best part: no gigafactories needed, only workshops with electricians (Rebaba CircularHub).
